@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor #E8F0FA
  BorderColor #4A6FA5
}
skinparam package {
  BackgroundColor #FDFDFD
  BorderColor #999999
}

title How a call is routed through ContractType

package "Contract author's crate" {
  component "MyToken\ncontractimpl(contracttrait)" as MyToken #FFF6E0
}

package "stellar-tokens::fungible" {
  component "FungibleToken\n(contracttrait)" as FT #FFF6E0
  component "ContractOverrides\n(internal plumbing)" as CO #FFF6E0

  component "Base" as Base
  component "AllowList" as AL
  component "BlockList" as BL
  component "RWA" as RWA

  component "storage.rs\nBase::transfer\nBase::mint\nBase::approve ..." as Storage
}

MyToken -down-> FT : implements and picks\nthe ContractType

FT -down-> CO : each method delegates to\nSelf::ContractType::<method>

CO <|.. Base
CO <|.. AL
CO <|.. BL
CO <|.. RWA

Base -down-> Storage : vanilla logic
AL -down-> Storage : allowlist check,\nthen vanilla logic
BL -down-> Storage : blocklist check,\nthen vanilla logic
RWA -down-> Storage : compliance and\nidentity checks

note right of FT
  ContractType is a single associated type.

  FungibleAllowList requires
    FungibleToken<ContractType = AllowList>
  FungibleBlockList requires
    FungibleToken<ContractType = BlockList>

  Implementing both on one contract
  cannot type-check.
end note

@enduml
